  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AL-01 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed at the campaign level and is discussed throughout the narrative; however, individual validation result records were not uniformly linked to UQ artifacts — approximately half of the ValidationResult entries carry no hasUncertaintyQuantification link, leaving aleatory uncertainty uncharacterized at the per-result level. This constitutes the W-AL-01 weakness targeted by this adversarial sample. Decision: Accepted (for test purposes).",
